This paper deals with analyzing the internal representations of neural networks and their ability to perform compositional tasks. The paper proposes a technique called ROLE that detects whether these representations implicitly encode symbolic structure. This falls under the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV). However, since the paper primarily focuses on natural language processing and machine learning, cs.CL and cs.LG are the most likely categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CV.
